  Next.js bridges this gap through multiple rendering strategies:
  
  - **Static Site Generation (SSG)**: Pre-renders pages at build time
  - **Server-Side Rendering (SSR)**: Renders pages on each request
  - **Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR)**: Combines static generation with dynamic updates
  
  ```
  // Example: Understanding rendering impact on SEO
  // This component would be invisible to crawlers in pure CSR
  export default function ProductPage({ product }) {
    const [reviews, setReviews] = useState([]);
  
    // ❌ Client-side data fetching - not SEO friendly
    useEffect(() => {
      fetch(`/api/reviews/${product.id}`)
        .then(res => res.json())
        .then(setReviews);
    }, [product.id]);
  
    return (
      <div>
        <h1>{product.name}</h1>
        {reviews.map(review => (
          <div key={review.id}>{review.content}</div>
        ))}
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```
  
  ## Core Web Vitals: The Performance-SEO Connection
  
  Google’s Core Web Vitals directly impact search rankings. Next.js 15+ provides several optimization features:
  
  - **Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)**: Target under 2.5 seconds
  - **First Input Delay (FID)**: Target under 100 milliseconds
  - **Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)**: Target under 0.1
  
